,309924,'EN','','Natural Wines from Aude'),(219758,14752,309925,'EN',NULL,'<em>White</em>'),(219759,14752,309926,'EN',NULL,'<em>soft white</em>'),(219760,14752,309929,'EN','','<em>dry white</em>'),(219761,14752,310439,'EN','The classic','Minced beef, Pavé d\'Isigny cheese, salad, pickles and barbecue sauce'),(219762,14752,312572,'EN','Cheese platter \"from here\" only from local producers!!','<strong>Sébastien de Cambremer</strong> uses for his creations only milk from the Mercher farm in Beaufour-Druval, Tomme de Cambremer, La Tomme de Papa au Poivre noir Sauvage, Le Choubi. <strong>The Montavigny farm in Criqueville</strong> uses organic milk from its Normandy cows to make us a Pont l\'évêque, a pavé d\'Auge and the Montavigny, and <strong>Gilles</strong> has his farm next to Livarot \" <strong>La ferme de la Biquetière</strong> \" he makes all our goat cheese.<br /> Apple jelly from Mémé which is in Manerbe and semi-salted butter from the Croix l\'Abbé farm in Manerbe.<br /> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>+4 euros on your menu</strong></span>'),(219763,14752,314074,'EN',NULL,''),(219765,14752,315739,'EN','Apple Cider Sorbet ',''),(219766,14752,319908,'EN','Minced beef burger with local Tomme cheese, fries',''),(219767,14752,320878,'EN','Richard',''),(219769,14752,332922,'EN','Monkey shoulder (Scotland)','Smooth, creamy, supple and very Malty'),(219770,14752,332923,'EN','Aberlour 10 years (Scotland)','Rich with a subtle dry and fresh aroma combined with the fruitiness of apples and pears of early autumn, supported by notes of vanilla and minty caramel.'),(219771,14752,332924,'EN','Lagavulin 16 years (Scotland)','Powerful aroma of peat smoke and seaweed, with deep woody notes'),(219772,14752,332925,'EN','The Glenlivet (Scotland)','Sweet notes of orange and pear with a tangy hint of apple.'),(219773,14752,332930,'EN','Vermouth dry tonic','Noilly Prat Gin sparkling water orange zest'),(219774,14752,333122,'EN','','19% Meunier for character and richness.<br /> 51% Chardonnay for deliciousness and tonicity.<br /> 30% Pinot noir for structure and tension'),(219775,14752,333123,'EN',NULL,'<p>50% Pinot Noir gives lightness, tenderness and fruitiness.<br /> 40% Chardonnay brings freshness and lemony notes.<br /> 10% Meunier ensures roundness and suppleness.</p>'),(219776,14752,333134,'EN','','This champagne of rare finesse is made exclusively from the best Crus of the white Champagne grape variety, Chardonnay. The three pillars of this Blanc de Blanc come from three famous Champagne Grands Crus: Avize, Oger and Chouilly, bringing strength, elegance and finesse to the wine.'),(219777,14752,333141,'EN',NULL,'Excellence, the hand-sewn prestige cuvée from Maison Collet is a sparkling interpretation of Haute Couture, produced from a blend of 11 Premiers and Grands Crus selected in 2014.<br /> 60% Chardonnay vinified in oak barrels.<br /> 40% Pinot Noir structures the wine and gives it softness and suppleness. Served with its elegant box.'),(219778,14752,333154,'EN','','Deep black color with a powerful nose, finely wooded with aromas of ripe fruit. Full and silky mouthfeel with good length.<br /><br /><div> 90% Merlot.<br /> 10% Malbec.</div>'),(219779,14752,333156,'EN','','An intense black dress. On the nose, jammy aromas of ripe black fruits blossom on a vanilla and spicy background. Am a rich, ample, gourmand, structured palate. The fruit, grilled and liquorice accompanies and pleasantly concludes the tasting.<br /> 70% Merlot<br /> 30%¨Malbec'),(219780,14752,333170,'EN','','A deep and generous Beaune premier cru: the nose is marked by black fruits such as blueberry and blackberry, the palate reveals a beautiful richness with tannins which lengthen the finish superbly. A great Côte de Beaune wine!'),(219781,14752,333171,'EN','','This wine goes well with cheeses, game and meats in brown sauce, grilled and roasted meats'),(219782,14752,333172,'EN','','Anecdotes ...<br /> Petit Chablis is harvested near the famous Kimmeridgian terroir, dating from the secondary era (150 million years),<br /> composed of calcareous sediments which give the wine a fine, mineral style with a fruity bouquet.<br /> Grapes that have reached optimum maturity which suggest that this Chablis is a success. Beautiful balance for this<br /> white.'),(219783,14752,333173,'EN','','Pale yellow color, fruity nose with notes of toasted bread, very fine palate, flavor of yellow almond fruits, good length on the palate, slightly vanilla'),(219785,14752,333175,'EN','','Pretty purple red color with brilliant reflections on the nose, this Châteauneuf-du-Pape develops aromas of small red fruits. Its mouth is full, silky and velvety'),(219787,14752,333184,'EN','','THE TASTING :<br /> Eye: pretty ruby color<br /> Nose: aromas of raspberry and violet<br /> Mouth: beautiful harmony of flavors, supple and generous, velvety tannins<br /> The work is traditional in the vineyards which are managed using sustainable agriculture. The age of the vines is 15 to<br /> 35 years.<br /> This Saumur-Champigny “Cuvée Traditionnelle” has been worked and rewarded for its elegance, suppleness and<br /> his generosity.'),(219789,14752,333190,'EN','','THE TASTING :<br /> Eye: pretty ruby color, brilliant<br /> Nose: aromas of red and black fruits which dominate (blackcurrant, blackberries, raspberry)<br /> Palate: discreet woody, soft and melted tannins, aromas of ripe fruit always present<br /> This red Sancerre from Domaine Vatan is made up of a quarter aged in oak barrels before blending, which<br /> makes a wine of character. A wine with aromas of ripe fruit on the nose and palate, a long and warm finish.<br /> A gourmet wine to enjoy quickly!'),(219791,14752,333193,'EN','','A happy estate, Clos des Sables, an exceptional dry white produced on a rare terroir, the balance, richness and precision of its aromas make this wine, 100% Chenin, a unique vintage.'),(219792,14752,333449,'EN','Spicy mojito at Jack Daniel\'s Fire','Jack Daniel\'s Fire, Lime, chili syrup, mint, ginger beer'),(219793,14752,333450,'EN','Samui Mojito Thai','Rum Morgan Spiced gold, coriander, lime, ginger syrup, ginger beer'),(219794,14752,333478,'EN','',''),(219795,14752,334314,'EN','Complete Slate Formula:','Starter + main course + dessert = 36€<br /> (Burgers and Poutines are not part of the Slate menu)'),(219796,14752,334315,'EN','Slate Formula 2 choices:','Starter + main course or Main course + dessert = 30€<br /> (Burgers and Poutines are not part of the Slate menu)'),(219797,14752,334316,'EN','Entrance','Greek Salad: Cucumber, tomato, olive, long pepper, red onion, Feta<br /> Or<br /> Salmon gravlax, mango chutney'),(219798,14752,334317,'EN','Dish of the day ','100% local horse steak, fries<br /> Or<br /> Sète land and sea, olives and peppers. Rice'),(219799,14752,334318,'EN','Dessert ','Cracker cabbage, caramel mango insert and whipped mascarpone<br /> Or<br /> Mille feuille, salted butter caramel and whipped mascarpone'),(219800,14752,334758,'EN','Glass of brut champagne',''),(219801,14752,334761,'EN','Champagne Palmer & Co','19% Meunier for character and richness.<br /> 51% Chardonnay for deliciousness and tonicity.<br /> 30% Pinot noir for structure and tension'),(219802,14752,334762,'EN','Bulle Royale dry white wine without alcohol ','Loire House Ackerman'),(219803,14752,334763,'EN','Champagne Pamer &ca, Blanc de Blanc, Premier Cru ','This champagne of rare finesse is made exclusively from the best Crus of the white Champagne grape variety, Chardonnay. The three pillars of this Blanc de Blanc come from three famous Champagne Grands Crus: Avize, Oger and Chouilly, bringing strength, elegance and finesse to the wine.'),(219804,14752,334764,'EN','Champagne Collet Esprit Couture 2014 Premier Cru','Excellence, the hand-sewn prestige cuvée from Maison Collet is a sparkling interpretation of Haute Couture, produced from a blend of 11 Premiers and Grands Crus selected in 2012.<br /> 60% Chardonnay vinified in oak barrels.<br /> 40% Pinot Noir structures the wine and gives it softness and suppleness. Served with its elegant box.'),(219805,14752,334806,'EN','','Fruity white wine'),(219806,14752,335487,'EN','Farm cider from Denis',''),(219807,14752,335488,'EN','Organic Poiré from the Desvoye cider house',''),(219808,14752,335489,'EN','Apple juice from the Desvoye cider house',''),(219809,14752,335490,'EN','Calvados from the Desvoye “Fine” cider farm',''),(219810,14752,335491,'EN','Calvados Schumberger Primat 3 years',''),(219811,14752,335492,'EN','Honey from the Dauge region 2025 from Beaufour-Druval','Anne Elise and Thoma'),(219812,14752,335493,'EN','Smoked trout rillettes or black pudding terrine with La Falaise apples that blush','The best of Normandy\'s terroire'),(219813,14752,335821,'EN','',''),(219814,14752,335823,'EN','',''),(219815,14752,335829,'EN',NULL,'Red'),(219816,14752,335830,'EN',NULL,'Red'),(219817,14752,335831,'EN',NULL,'Red'),(219818,14752,336751,'EN','Apple jelly from grandma\'s','Apple jelly made by grandma with her apples, sugar, lemon juice and that\'s it!'),(219819,14752,336752,'EN','Gift box 3 bottles of wine','A Beaujolais château with red flowers<br /> A Rhonea white Côtes-du-Rhône, an OCD legend<br /> A rosé Bordeaux Montfollet-le-valentin'),(219820,14752,337816,'EN','Poached baba bouchon with a Mojito touch, whipped cream ','Lime cream, lemon tarragon sorbet'),(219822,14752,346882,'EN','Calvados from the Desvoyes cider farm \"15 years\"','Local Calvados less than 1 km'),(219823,14752,346883,'EN','Calvados from the Denis cider farm \"15 years\"',''),(219824,14752,346884,'EN','Distillerie des Ambres 14 years minimum','SCHLUMBERGER PRIMATE FAMILY'),(219825,14752,347949,'EN',NULL,''),(219826,14752,347950,'EN','','Pretty purple red color with brilliant reflections on the nose, this Châteauneuf-du-Pape develops aromas of small red fruit. Its mouth is full, silky and velvety'),(219827,14752,351382,'EN','','Anecdotes...<br /> After night harvests, skin maceration is carried out over several hours. There is then pressing<br /> pneumatic without oxygen, cold liquid stabilization, then fermentation at low temperature.<br /> Aging on fine lees finally ensures the best conditions for the evolution of aromas.'),(219828,14752,355692,'EN','','Aude wine NATURAL WINE'),(219829,14752,357647,'EN',NULL,'Pretty candy pink color with Chinese pearl highlights. Elegant nose of crushed strawberries, redcurrants and blueberries. Round and silky mouth. Aromas of raspberry compote, garrigue strawberries and red fruit liqueur combined with aromas of cane sugar. Nice length.'),(219830,14752,357873,'EN','Homemade Lemon Sorbet',''),(219831,14752,357874,'EN','Sicilian Mandarin Sorbet',''),(219832,14752,357875,'EN','Timut pear and pepper sorbet',''),(219837,14752,361599,'EN','','Eye: bright white, slightly yellow gold<br /> Nose: delicate notes of white flowers (acacia, cherry), fruit (pear, melon) and a touch of mint.<br /> Mouth: round and suave with a lovely mineral, iodized finish.<br /> This Pouilly-Fumé is quite simply a success and a beautiful harmony!'),(219838,14752,361600,'EN','',''),(219839,14752,361601,'EN','','The Beaumes-de-Venise appellation is an appellation of the Rhône Valley, recognized as AOC in 1937, and qualified in 2005 as \"Cru des Côtes du Rhône\". The vineyard occupies the hillsides of the south-southeast slope of the Dentelles de Montmirail.<br /><br /> The main grape variety of AOC Beaumes-de-Venise is Grenache noir for at least 50% and the complementary grape variety is Syrah for a minimum of 25%. Grape varieties such as Mourvèdre, Cinsault and other grape varieties authorized in the Rhône Valley can be added with the possibility of 10% white grape variety.<br /> THE TASTING :<br /> Eye: beautiful ruby color<br /> Nose: with aromas of red fruits, notably cherry, with notes of spices<br /> Mouth: we find aromas of red fruits, with notes of prunes. Good power and length.'),(219840,14752,361602,'EN','','Coming from organic farming, this Côtes du Rhône red AOP from the Lafond Roc-Epine estate comes from soil<br /> stony and clay-limestone for one plot, sandy and rolled pebbles for the second. The Lafond estate<br /> wants to bring freshness and good fruitiness to a powerful wine from the Rhône Valley.<br /> THE TASTING :<br /> Eye: pretty dark red color<br /> Nose: bouquet of flavors dominated by ripe fruits, cherries, blackcurrant and undergrowth<br /> Mouth: concentrated and velvety, all roundness'),(219841,14752,361603,'EN','','Anecdotes...<br /> This Mâcon-Pierreclos red 2022 was harvested at optimum maturity. The harvest is sorted and destemmed before<br /><br /> macerate for six to seven days in vats. This vinification process makes it possible to extract the color and tannins from this Mâcon-<br /> Pierreclos. Temperatures are controlled during this process. The wine is then aged for six months in vats before<br /> to be bottled in spring.<br /> THE TASTING :<br /> Eye: ruby red color with purplish reflections<br /> Nose: expressive, with aromas of red and black fruits (raspberry, cherry, blackcurrant)<br /> Mouth: velvety, gourmand, with lots of roundness and lovely length'),(219843,14752,361809,'EN','Plate of dry sausage with nuts',''),(219844,14752,361810,'EN','White cheese with salted butter caramel and chocolate bar chips',''),(219846,14752,362574,'EN','Vanilla ice cream',''),(219849,14752,362578,'EN','Roubignôles Raspberry 300 ml',''),(219850,14752,362579,'EN','The boss\'s prunes 100 ml',''),(219851,14752,364428,'EN','Jomo Peach Hibiscus Iced White Tea','Jomo is a healthy organic still drink made in France'),(219852,14752,364429,'EN','Jomo Ginger Iced Lemonade','Jomo is a healthy organic still drink made in France'),(219853,14752,364430,'EN','Jomo Mango Iced Lemonade','Jomo is a healthy organic still drink made in France'),(219854,14752,364431,'EN','Jomo Mint Lemon Green Tea Iced Detox','Jomo is a healthy organic still drink made in France'),(219855,14752,364529,'EN','Homemade Cara